subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia
: Male—Median process of pygophore (
Fig. 46
) with rounded apical part and very small tapered apex (
Fig. 51
). Both parameres slender with medium-sized setae on outer side and inner side, and with sharp apices (
Figs. 47–50
). Right paramere distinctly emarginated medially on inner view (
Fig. 49
). Pedicel relatively robust and bent laterally (
Figs. 53, 54
). Basal lobe of dorsal phallothecal sclerite enlarged on right side (
Fig. 52
). Dorsal endosomal sclerite corrugated (
Fig. 54
).

Female—Valvifer I subquadrangular with curvature on posterior margin and dense, short setae on outer side (
Fig. 45
). Styloids on inner margin with dense, short setae and with sharp apex, inner margins curved on more than 1/3 of length (
Fig. 43
). Basal part of valvula II with process convolute inwards and forked (
Fig. 44
). Apical part with one small sharp process and distinctly rounded apex (
Fig. 44
).
